JOHANNESBURG Former Golden Lions and current Scotland number eight Josh Strauss has been ruled out of the remainder of the Six Nations through injury.READ: Golden Lions pen new equipment deal Rhino Rugby SAStrauss, 30, sustained a kidney injury in his side s 22-16 defeat to France at the Stade de France last week.Strauss will return to Glasgow Warriors for his recovery, and a review of his injury is scheduled in six weeks. After completing the [French] match, he was scanned in Paris, said Scottish Rugby. Both the scan, and the player, were reviewed back in Scotland, where the full extent of the injury was confirmed. African News Agency